-- United Utilities Says Steve Mogford to Become Chief Executive in January
-- B y   K a r i   L u n d g r e n
-- 2010-11-22T10:45:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-22/united-utilities-says-steve-mogford-to-become-chief-executive-in-january.html
United Utilities Group Plc , the
U.K.’s largest publicly traded water company, said  Steve Mogford 
has been appointed chief executive officer, taking over from
Philip Green.  Mogford, 54, will become chief executive designate and a
board member on Jan. 5, the Warrington, England-based water
company said in a statement today. Green plans to step down on
March 31. He was appointed in 2006.  Mogford comes to United Utilities from the defense
industry, where he has held executive positions at BAE systems
Plc and British Aerospace Plc, the company said.  “We have a clear plan to invest a record 3.6 billion
($5.78 billion) in the North West over the next five years and
Steve is the right man to lead that investment program,”
Chairman John McAdam said in the statement.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Kari Lundgren in London at 
 klundgren2@bloomberg.net  